article.headline: Long Island U. 70, Columbia 60
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Kellen Allen scored 19 points to help Long Island U beat Columbia 70-60 on Tuesday night. Eugene Kotorobai had 15 points and Kyle Johnson added 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Blackbirds (2-1), who were tied 35-35 at the half. Jaytornah Wisseh finished with 13. Nike Scott had 14 points and Ben Nwachukwu added 12 for Columbia (1-4). Trailing 39-38, LIU went on an 8-0 run to take a 46-39 lead with 13:29 left in the game. The Lions closed to 54-51 on Scott's 3-pointer with 5:50 left, but the Blackbirds scored the next six points to put the game away.
